Concrete plumbline prototype (2-3 hour build, fits in $25 budget for ~150 problems at 3 iter @ 1500 toks each): ```python
def extract_with_refinement(contract, k=3):
    context = base_prompt(contract)
    history = []
    for i in range(k):
        cand = llm_extract(context, history)
        verdict, reason = validator.check(cand)
        if verdict == 'accept':
            return cand, i+1
        if verdict == 'refute' and reason in [h[1] for h in history]:
            return None, i+1  # no-progress stop (Houdini-style fixpoint)
        history.append((cand, reason))
        context = add_refute_to_context(context, cand, reason)
    return cand, k  # return last attempt even if not accepted
``` Stop-on-no-change is the critical guard against oscillation; the literature shows fixed k without it produces self-bias degradation.

